    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That sounds like a good start. I want to make sure I'm being thorough though. Some people argue that this kind of interpretation is a huge stretch of the Constitution and that it basically lets judges make up laws based on their own values instead of following what's actually written. How should I address those criticisms in my lesson so it doesn't seem like I'm just ignoring the legal opposition?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
