      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You can acknowledge the criticism by framing it as a debate between judicial activism and strict textualism, but then argue that substantive due process is necessary because the Constitution's text is silent on many evolving societal needs like privacy and bodily autonomy. By relying on historical traditions and fundamental human dignity rather than just the letter of the law, judges ensure that rights grow alongside our society instead of stagnating. This approach empowers the judiciary to act as a guardian of liberty when the legislative branch fails to protect vulnerable groups.",
