      "content": "Thanks. I'm a bit worried about that \"argue that\" part tho. If I tell my students that the best way to handle the opposition is to just argue against them, it might feel like I'm pushing a specific political view rather than teaching them how to weigh different legal frameworks. Is there a way to represent the textualist/originalist view that makes it sound like a legitimate legal philosophy rather than just a way to block progress?",
