    "summary": "The user, playing the role of a teacher, asks for help drafting a civics lesson on substantive due process, initially requesting a focus on its benefits for civil rights. After the user expresses concern about appearing biased, the assistant provides advice on how to frame the debate, eventually helping the user represent the opposition's view more legitimately.",
